FILE: admin.rs
MOD: api/admin
ROLE: Admin router — operator-level endpoints for project management, stats, suspension, and cascade deletion
EP: admin_router; list_projects; get_stats; project_stats; delete_project; suspend_project; unsuspend_project
STAB: volatile
INV:
  - All admin handlers require AdminAuth — zero shared code with ProjectAuth or AgentAuth
  - delete_project MUST call disconnect_all_in_project() BEFORE repo.delete_project() — mandatory ordering
  - Swapping the order creates a ghost-session window: live WS sessions could attempt delivery into a deleted project
  - suspend_project and unsuspend_project set project status TEXT — enforcement is in verify_project_key (transparent to all callers)
  - Admin handlers access repo via state.broker.repo — same path as regular handlers, not a bypass
  - AdminAuth returns 503 if BROKER_ADMIN_KEY env var not set (admin API disabled), 401 if key wrong
  - No admin operation touches body content or stanza routing logic
LOOK: delete_project handler comment; disconnect_all_in_project in state.rs; verify_project_key status check in repository.rs
CHK: arch validate && arch index after changes; verify disconnect before delete ordering in tests
CNTR: api/admin::delete_project depends_on broker/state::disconnect_all_in_project
CNTR: api/admin::delete_project depends_on db/repository::delete_project
DEPS-ON: broker/state; db/repository; api/auth
